# Atlas portal — runtime configuration template.
#
# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and fill real values for YOUR environment.
# Everything here is a FICTIONAL placeholder — never commit real hosts/tokens.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Dev data source (MSW seam — plan 018 P1 / 026). Controls whether `pnpm dev`
# serves deterministic fixtures or hits real source systems:
#   • no Confluence creds set  → dev AUTO-MOCKS (MSW fixtures); zero-config onboarding
#   • real Confluence creds    → dev hits the REAL source systems
#   • DEV_MOCKS=1              → force mock (E2E uses this; hermetic regardless of creds)
#   • DEV_MOCKS=0              → force real (debug the real path without full creds)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Dev mock seam ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEV_MOCKS=1
# DEV_MOCK_LATENCY_MS=400                # add latency to mocked fetches (test deferred UI)

# ── Source systems · Confluence (live discovery + content + policies) ────────
# LEFT COMMENTED so a fresh `cp portal/.env.example portal/.env.local` stays in
# zero-config MOCK mode (presence of BASE_URL + TOKEN is what flips dev to real;
# committing them active would make a just-copied env hit a fake live endpoint).
# Uncomment + fill real values to run dev against live Confluence.
# CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL=https://your-org.atlassian.net/wiki
# CONFLUENCE_EMAIL=you@your-org.example
# CONFLUENCE_TOKEN=replace-with-confluence-api-token
# CONFLUENCE_SPACE_KEYS=CLOUD                  # reference-discovery spaces (comma-separated)
# CONFLUENCE_SECURITY_SPACE_KEY=SECPOL         # security-policy space key
# Security policies may live in a SEPARATE Confluence instance — override per channel
# (each falls back to the main CONFLUENCE_* above when unset):
# CONFLUENCE_SECURITY_BASE_URL=https://security.your-org.atlassian.net/wiki
# CONFLUENCE_SECURITY_TOKEN=replace-with-security-confluence-token
# CONFLUENCE_SECURITY_EMAIL=you@your-org.example
# Availability-matrix page id per landing zone: CONFLUENCE_AVAILABILITY_PAGE_<LZ>
# CONFLUENCE_AVAILABILITY_PAGE_AWSF=000000
# CONFLUENCE_AVAILABILITY_PAGE_AZURE=000000
# CONFLUENCE_RELEASE_NOTES_PAGE_ID=000000      # "What's New" newsletter page id

# ── Source systems · Terraform registry ──────────────────────────────────────
# TERRAFORM_BASE_URL=https://tfe.your-org.example
# TERRAFORM_TOKEN=replace-with-terraform-api-token

# ── Source systems · Guidance store ──────────────────────────────────────────
# GUIDANCE_URL=https://guidance.your-org.example/guidance

# ── Content cache (optional — in-memory if unset) ────────────────────────────
# CACHE_VALKEY_URL=redis://localhost:6379
# CACHE_VALKEY_CLIENT=default
# CACHE_TTL_SECONDS=300
# CACHE_MAX_ENTRIES=1000

# ── Ask / LLM provider (default: simulated — deterministic, no external calls) ─
# LLM_PROVIDER=simulated                  # 'bedrock' | 'rai' | unset/simulated
# Bedrock:
# BEDROCK_MODEL_ID=anthropic.claude-x
# BEDROCK_REGION=us-east-1                # falls back to AWS_REGION
# RAI (OAuth-style gateway):
# RAI_BASE_URL=https://rai.your-org.example
# RAI_TOKEN_URL=https://rai.your-org.example/oauth/token
# RAI_CLIENT_ID=replace-with-client-id
# RAI_CLIENT_SECRET=replace-with-client-secret
# RAI_MODEL_ID=replace-with-model-id

# ── Portal server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PORTAL_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000     # canonical origin (absolute URLs / SSR)
# CONTEXT_API_BASE_URL=                   # set ONLY to call context-layer over HTTP; default is in-process
# PORT=3000                               # dev/prod (Nitro) server port

# ── Infra / lambda deployment (NOT read by the portal dev runtime) ───────────
# REGISTRY_TABLE, FEEDBACK_TABLE, RUNTIME_SECRET, and AWS_* credentials belong to
# the context-layer lambda deployment config, not this file.
